7683ASTImporter::~ASTImporter() = default;
7684
7685Optional<unsigned> ASTImporter::getFieldIndex(Decl *F) {
7686 assert(F && (isa<FieldDecl>(*F) || isa<IndirectFieldDecl>(*F)) &&
7687 "Try to get field index for non-field.");
7688
7689 auto *Owner = dyn_cast<RecordDecl>(F->getDeclContext());
7690 if (!Owner)
7691 return None;
7692
7693 unsigned Index = 0;
7694 for (const auto *D : Owner->decls()) {
7695 if (D == F)
7696 return Index;
7697
7698 if (isa<FieldDecl>(*D) || isa<IndirectFieldDecl>(*D))
7699 ++Index;
7700 }
7701
7702 llvm_unreachable("Field was not found in its parent context.");
7703
7704 return None;
7705}
7706
7707ASTImporter::FoundDeclsTy
7708ASTImporter::findDeclsInToCtx(DeclContext *DC, DeclarationName Name) {
7709 // We search in the redecl context because of transparent contexts.
7710 // E.g. a simple C language enum is a transparent context:
7711 // enum E { A, B };
7712 // Now if we had a global variable in the TU
7713 // int A;
7714 // then the enum constant 'A' and the variable 'A' violates ODR.
7715 // We can diagnose this only if we search in the redecl context.
7716 DeclContext *ReDC = DC->getRedeclContext();
7717 if (LookupTable) {
7718 ASTImporterLookupTable::LookupResult LookupResult =
7719 LookupTable->lookup(ReDC, Name);
7720 return FoundDeclsTy(LookupResult.begin(), LookupResult.end());
7721 } else {
7722 // FIXME Can we remove this kind of lookup?
7723 // Or lldb really needs this C/C++ lookup?
7724 FoundDeclsTy Result;
7725 ReDC->localUncachedLookup(Name, Result);
7726 return Result;
7727 }
7728}
7729
7730void ASTImporter::AddToLookupTable(Decl *ToD) {
7731 if (LookupTable)
7732 if (auto *ToND = dyn_cast<NamedDecl>(ToD))
7733 LookupTable->add(ToND);
7734}
7735
7736Expected<Decl *> ASTImporter::ImportImpl(Decl *FromD) {
7737 // Import the decl using ASTNodeImporter.
7738 ASTNodeImporter Importer(*this);
7739 return Importer.Visit(FromD);
7740}
7741
7742void ASTImporter::RegisterImportedDecl(Decl *FromD, Decl *ToD) {
7743 MapImported(FromD, ToD);
7744 AddToLookupTable(ToD);
7745}
7746
7747Expected<QualType> ASTImporter::Import(QualType FromT) {
7748 if (FromT.isNull())
7749 return QualType{};
7750
7751 const Type *FromTy = FromT.getTypePtr();
7752
7753 // Check whether we've already imported this type.
7754 llvm::DenseMap<const Type *, const Type *>::iterator Pos
7755 = ImportedTypes.find(FromTy);
7756 if (Pos != ImportedTypes.end())
7757 return ToContext.getQualifiedType(Pos->second, FromT.getLocalQualifiers());
7758
7759 // Import the type
7760 ASTNodeImporter Importer(*this);
7761 ExpectedType ToTOrErr = Importer.Visit(FromTy);
7762 if (!ToTOrErr)
7763 return ToTOrErr.takeError();
7764
7765 // Record the imported type.
7766 ImportedTypes[FromTy] = (*ToTOrErr).getTypePtr();
7767
7768 return ToContext.getQualifiedType(*ToTOrErr, FromT.getLocalQualifiers());
7769}
7770
7771Expected<TypeSourceInfo *> ASTImporter::Import(TypeSourceInfo *FromTSI) {
7772 if (!FromTSI)
7773 return FromTSI;
7774
7775 // FIXME: For now we just create a "trivial" type source info based
7776 // on the type and a single location. Implement a real version of this.
7777 ExpectedType TOrErr = Import(FromTSI->getType());
7778 if (!TOrErr)
7779 return TOrErr.takeError();
7780 ExpectedSLoc BeginLocOrErr = Import(FromTSI->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc());
7781 if (!BeginLocOrErr)
7782 return BeginLocOrErr.takeError();
7783
7784 return ToContext.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(*TOrErr, *BeginLocOrErr);
7785}
7786
7787Expected<Attr *> ASTImporter::Import(const Attr *FromAttr) {
7788 Attr *ToAttr = FromAttr->clone(ToContext);
7789 if (auto ToRangeOrErr = Import(FromAttr->getRange()))
7790 ToAttr->setRange(*ToRangeOrErr);
7791 else
7792 return ToRangeOrErr.takeError();
7793
7794 return ToAttr;
7795}
7796
7797Decl *ASTImporter::GetAlreadyImportedOrNull(const Decl *FromD) const {
7798 auto Pos = ImportedDecls.find(FromD);
7799 if (Pos != ImportedDecls.end())
7800 return Pos->second;
7801 else
7802 return nullptr;
7803}
7804
7805TranslationUnitDecl *ASTImporter::GetFromTU(Decl *ToD) {
7806 auto FromDPos = ImportedFromDecls.find(ToD);
7807 if (FromDPos == ImportedFromDecls.end())
7808 return nullptr;
7809 return FromDPos->second->getTranslationUnitDecl();
7810}
7811
7812Expected<Decl *> ASTImporter::Import(Decl *FromD) {
7813 if (!FromD)
7814 return nullptr;
7815
7816
7817 // Check whether we've already imported this declaration.
7818 Decl *ToD = GetAlreadyImportedOrNull(FromD);
7819 if (ToD) {
7820 // If FromD has some updated flags after last import, apply it
7821 updateFlags(FromD, ToD);
7822 return ToD;
7823 }
7824
7825 // Import the declaration.
7826 ExpectedDecl ToDOrErr = ImportImpl(FromD);
7827 if (!ToDOrErr)
7828 return ToDOrErr;
7829 ToD = *ToDOrErr;
7830
7831 // FIXME Use getImportDeclErrorIfAny() here (and return with the error) once
7832 // the error handling is finished in GetImportedOrCreateSpecialDecl().
7833 if (!ToD) {
7834 return nullptr;
7835 }
7836
7837 // Make sure that ImportImpl registered the imported decl.
7838 assert(ImportedDecls.count(FromD) != 0 && "Missing call to MapImported?");
7839
7840 // Once the decl is connected to the existing declarations, i.e. when the
7841 // redecl chain is properly set then we populate the lookup again.
7842 // This way the primary context will be able to find all decls.
7843 AddToLookupTable(ToD);
7844
7845 // Notify subclasses.
7846 Imported(FromD, ToD);
7847
7848 updateFlags(FromD, ToD);
7849 return ToDOrErr;
7850}
7851
7852Expected<DeclContext *> ASTImporter::ImportContext(DeclContext *FromDC) {
7853 if (!FromDC)
7854 return FromDC;
7855
7856 ExpectedDecl ToDCOrErr = Import(cast<Decl>(FromDC));
7857 if (!ToDCOrErr)
7858 return ToDCOrErr.takeError();
7859 auto *ToDC = cast<DeclContext>(*ToDCOrErr);
7860
7861 // When we're using a record/enum/Objective-C class/protocol as a context, we
7862 // need it to have a definition.
7863 if (auto *ToRecord = dyn_cast<RecordDecl>(ToDC)) {
7864 auto *FromRecord = cast<RecordDecl>(FromDC);
7865 if (ToRecord->isCompleteDefinition()) {
7866 // Do nothing.
7867 } else if (FromRecord->isCompleteDefinition()) {
7868 if (Error Err = ASTNodeImporter(*this).ImportDefinition(
7869 FromRecord, ToRecord, ASTNodeImporter::IDK_Basic))
7870 return std::move(Err);
7871 } else {
7872 CompleteDecl(ToRecord);
7873 }
7874 } else if (auto *ToEnum = dyn_cast<EnumDecl>(ToDC)) {
7875 auto *FromEnum = cast<EnumDecl>(FromDC);
7876 if (ToEnum->isCompleteDefinition()) {
7877 // Do nothing.
7878 } else if (FromEnum->isCompleteDefinition()) {
7879 if (Error Err = ASTNodeImporter(*this).ImportDefinition(
7880 FromEnum, ToEnum, ASTNodeImporter::IDK_Basic))
7881 return std::move(Err);
7882 } else {
7883 CompleteDecl(ToEnum);
7884 }
7885 } else if (auto *ToClass = dyn_cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(ToDC)) {
7886 auto *FromClass = cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(FromDC);
7887 if (ToClass->getDefinition()) {
7888 // Do nothing.
7889 } else if (ObjCInterfaceDecl *FromDef = FromClass->getDefinition()) {
7890 if (Error Err = ASTNodeImporter(*this).ImportDefinition(
7891 FromDef, ToClass, ASTNodeImporter::IDK_Basic))
7892 return std::move(Err);
7893 } else {
7894 CompleteDecl(ToClass);
7895 }
7896 } else if (auto *ToProto = dyn_cast<ObjCProtocolDecl>(ToDC)) {
7897 auto *FromProto = cast<ObjCProtocolDecl>(FromDC);
7898 if (ToProto->getDefinition()) {
7899 // Do nothing.
7900 } else if (ObjCProtocolDecl *FromDef = FromProto->getDefinition()) {
7901 if (Error Err = ASTNodeImporter(*this).ImportDefinition(
7902 FromDef, ToProto, ASTNodeImporter::IDK_Basic))
7903 return std::move(Err);
7904 } else {
7905 CompleteDecl(ToProto);
7906 }
7907 }
7908
7909 return ToDC;
7910}
7911
7912Expected<Expr *> ASTImporter::Import(Expr *FromE) {
7913 if (ExpectedStmt ToSOrErr = Import(cast_or_null<Stmt>(FromE)))
7914 return cast_or_null<Expr>(*ToSOrErr);
7915 else
7916 return ToSOrErr.takeError();
7917}
7918
7919Expected<Stmt *> ASTImporter::Import(Stmt *FromS) {
7920 if (!FromS)
7921 return nullptr;
7922
7923 // Check whether we've already imported this statement.
7924 llvm::DenseMap<Stmt *, Stmt *>::iterator Pos = ImportedStmts.find(FromS);
7925 if (Pos != ImportedStmts.end())
7926 return Pos->second;
7927
7928 // Import the statement.
7929 ASTNodeImporter Importer(*this);
7930 ExpectedStmt ToSOrErr = Importer.Visit(FromS);
7931 if (!ToSOrErr)
7932 return ToSOrErr;
7933
7934 if (auto *ToE = dyn_cast<Expr>(*ToSOrErr)) {
7935 auto *FromE = cast<Expr>(FromS);
7936 // Copy ExprBitfields, which may not be handled in Expr subclasses
7937 // constructors.
7938 ToE->setValueKind(FromE->getValueKind());
7939 ToE->setObjectKind(FromE->getObjectKind());
7940 ToE->setTypeDependent(FromE->isTypeDependent());
7941 ToE->setValueDependent(FromE->isValueDependent());
7942 ToE->setInstantiationDependent(FromE->isInstantiationDependent());
7943 ToE->setContainsUnexpandedParameterPack(
7944 FromE->containsUnexpandedParameterPack());
7945 }
7946
7947 // Record the imported statement object.
7948 ImportedStmts[FromS] = *ToSOrErr;
7949 return ToSOrErr;
7950}
7951
7952Expected<NestedNameSpecifier *>
7953ASTImporter::Import(NestedNameSpecifier *FromNNS) {
7954 if (!FromNNS)
7955 return nullptr;
7956
7957 NestedNameSpecifier *Prefix;
7958 if (Error Err = importInto(Prefix, FromNNS->getPrefix()))
7959 return std::move(Err);
7960
7961 switch (FromNNS->getKind()) {
7962 case NestedNameSpecifier::Identifier:
7963 assert(FromNNS->getAsIdentifier() && "NNS should contain identifier.");
7964 return NestedNameSpecifier::Create(ToContext, Prefix,
7965 Import(FromNNS->getAsIdentifier()));
7966
7967 case NestedNameSpecifier::Namespace:
7968 if (ExpectedDecl NSOrErr = Import(FromNNS->getAsNamespace())) {
7969 return NestedNameSpecifier::Create(ToContext, Prefix,
7970 cast<NamespaceDecl>(*NSOrErr));
7971 } else
7972 return NSOrErr.takeError();
7973
7974 case NestedNameSpecifier::NamespaceAlias:
7975 if (ExpectedDecl NSADOrErr = Import(FromNNS->getAsNamespaceAlias()))
7976 return NestedNameSpecifier::Create(ToContext, Prefix,
7977 cast<NamespaceAliasDecl>(*NSADOrErr));
7978 else
7979 return NSADOrErr.takeError();
7980
7981 case NestedNameSpecifier::Global:
7982 return NestedNameSpecifier::GlobalSpecifier(ToContext);
7983
7984 case NestedNameSpecifier::Super:
7985 if (ExpectedDecl RDOrErr = Import(FromNNS->getAsRecordDecl()))
7986 return NestedNameSpecifier::SuperSpecifier(ToContext,
7987 cast<CXXRecordDecl>(*RDOrErr));
7988 else
7989 return RDOrErr.takeError();
7990
7991 case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpec:
7992 case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpecWithTemplate:
7993 if (Expected<QualType> TyOrErr =
7994 Import(QualType(FromNNS->getAsType(), 0u))) {
7995 bool TSTemplate =
7996 FromNNS->getKind() == NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpecWithTemplate;
7997 return NestedNameSpecifier::Create(ToContext, Prefix, TSTemplate,
7998 TyOrErr->getTypePtr());
7999 } else {
8000 return TyOrErr.takeError();
8001 }
8002 }
8003
8004 llvm_unreachable("Invalid nested name specifier kind");
8005}
8006
8007Expected<NestedNameSpecifierLoc>
8008ASTImporter::Import(NestedNameSpecifierLoc FromNNS) {
8009 // Copied from NestedNameSpecifier mostly.
8010 SmallVector<NestedNameSpecifierLoc , 8> NestedNames;
8011 NestedNameSpecifierLoc NNS = FromNNS;
8012
8013 // Push each of the nested-name-specifiers's onto a stack for
8014 // serialization in reverse order.
8015 while (NNS) {
8016 NestedNames.push_back(NNS);
8017 NNS = NNS.getPrefix();
8018 }
8019
8020 NestedNameSpecifierLocBuilder Builder;
8021
8022 while (!NestedNames.empty()) {
8023 NNS = NestedNames.pop_back_val();
8024 NestedNameSpecifier *Spec = nullptr;
8025 if (Error Err = importInto(Spec, NNS.getNestedNameSpecifier()))
8026 return std::move(Err);
8027
8028 NestedNameSpecifier::SpecifierKind Kind = Spec->getKind();
8029
8030 SourceLocation ToLocalBeginLoc, ToLocalEndLoc;
8031 if (Kind != NestedNameSpecifier::Super) {
8032 if (Error Err = importInto(ToLocalBeginLoc, NNS.getLocalBeginLoc()))
8033 return std::move(Err);
8034
8035 if (Kind != NestedNameSpecifier::Global)
8036 if (Error Err = importInto(ToLocalEndLoc, NNS.getLocalEndLoc()))
8037 return std::move(Err);
8038 }
8039
8040 switch (Kind) {
8041 case NestedNameSpecifier::Identifier:
8042 Builder.Extend(getToContext(), Spec->getAsIdentifier(), ToLocalBeginLoc,
8043 ToLocalEndLoc);
8044 break;
8045
8046 case NestedNameSpecifier::Namespace:
8047 Builder.Extend(getToContext(), Spec->getAsNamespace(), ToLocalBeginLoc,
8048 ToLocalEndLoc);
8049 break;
8050
8051 case NestedNameSpecifier::NamespaceAlias:
8052 Builder.Extend(getToContext(), Spec->getAsNamespaceAlias(),
8053 ToLocalBeginLoc, ToLocalEndLoc);
8054 break;
8055
8056 case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpec:
8057 case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpecWithTemplate: {
8058 SourceLocation ToTLoc;
8059 if (Error Err = importInto(ToTLoc, NNS.getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc()))
8060 return std::move(Err);
8061 TypeSourceInfo *TSI = getToContext().getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(
8062 QualType(Spec->getAsType(), 0), ToTLoc);
8063 Builder.Extend(getToContext(), ToLocalBeginLoc, TSI->getTypeLoc(),
8064 ToLocalEndLoc);
8065 break;
8066 }
8067
8068 case NestedNameSpecifier::Global:
8069 Builder.MakeGlobal(getToContext(), ToLocalBeginLoc);
8070 break;
8071
8072 case NestedNameSpecifier::Super: {
8073 auto ToSourceRangeOrErr = Import(NNS.getSourceRange());
8074 if (!ToSourceRangeOrErr)
8075 return ToSourceRangeOrErr.takeError();
8076
8077 Builder.MakeSuper(getToContext(), Spec->getAsRecordDecl(),
8078 ToSourceRangeOrErr->getBegin(),
8079 ToSourceRangeOrErr->getEnd());
8080 }
8081 }
8082 }
8083
8084 return Builder.getWithLocInContext(getToContext());
8085}
8086
8087Expected<TemplateName> ASTImporter::Import(TemplateName From) {
8088 switch (From.getKind()) {
8089 case TemplateName::Template:
8090 if (ExpectedDecl ToTemplateOrErr = Import(From.getAsTemplateDecl()))
8091 return TemplateName(cast<TemplateDecl>(*ToTemplateOrErr));
8092 else
8093 return ToTemplateOrErr.takeError();
8094
8095 case TemplateName::OverloadedTemplate: {
8096 OverloadedTemplateStorage *FromStorage = From.getAsOverloadedTemplate();
8097 UnresolvedSet<2> ToTemplates;
8098 for (auto *I : *FromStorage) {
8099 if (auto ToOrErr = Import(I))
8100 ToTemplates.addDecl(cast<NamedDecl>(*ToOrErr));
8101 else
8102 return ToOrErr.takeError();
8103 }
8104 return ToContext.getOverloadedTemplateName(ToTemplates.begin(),
8105 ToTemplates.end());
8106 }
8107
8108 case TemplateName::AssumedTemplate: {
8109 AssumedTemplateStorage *FromStorage = From.getAsAssumedTemplateName();
8110 auto DeclNameOrErr = Import(FromStorage->getDeclName());
8111 if (!DeclNameOrErr)
8112 return DeclNameOrErr.takeError();
8113 return ToContext.getAssumedTemplateName(*DeclNameOrErr);
8114 }
8115
8116 case TemplateName::QualifiedTemplate: {
8117 QualifiedTemplateName *QTN = From.getAsQualifiedTemplateName();
8118 auto QualifierOrErr = Import(QTN->getQualifier());
8119 if (!QualifierOrErr)
8120 return QualifierOrErr.takeError();
8121
8122 if (ExpectedDecl ToTemplateOrErr = Import(From.getAsTemplateDecl()))
8123 return ToContext.getQualifiedTemplateName(
8124 *QualifierOrErr, QTN->hasTemplateKeyword(),
8125 cast<TemplateDecl>(*ToTemplateOrErr));
8126 else
8127 return ToTemplateOrErr.takeError();
8128 }
8129
8130 case TemplateName::DependentTemplate: {
8131 DependentTemplateName *DTN = From.getAsDependentTemplateName();
8132 auto QualifierOrErr = Import(DTN->getQualifier());
8133 if (!QualifierOrErr)
8134 return QualifierOrErr.takeError();
8135
8136 if (DTN->isIdentifier()) {
8137 return ToContext.getDependentTemplateName(*QualifierOrErr,
8138 Import(DTN->getIdentifier()));
8139 }
8140
8141 return ToContext.getDependentTemplateName(*QualifierOrErr,
8142 DTN->getOperator());
8143 }
8144
8145 case TemplateName::SubstTemplateTemplateParm: {
8146 SubstTemplateTemplateParmStorage *Subst =
8147 From.getAsSubstTemplateTemplateParm();
8148 ExpectedDecl ParamOrErr = Import(Subst->getParameter());
8149 if (!ParamOrErr)
8150 return ParamOrErr.takeError();
8151
8152 auto ReplacementOrErr = Import(Subst->getReplacement());
8153 if (!ReplacementOrErr)
8154 return ReplacementOrErr.takeError();
8155
8156 return ToContext.getSubstTemplateTemplateParm(
8157 cast<TemplateTemplateParmDecl>(*ParamOrErr), *ReplacementOrErr);
8158 }
8159
8160 case TemplateName::SubstTemplateTemplateParmPack: {
8161 SubstTemplateTemplateParmPackStorage *SubstPack
8162 = From.getAsSubstTemplateTemplateParmPack();
8163 ExpectedDecl ParamOrErr = Import(SubstPack->getParameterPack());
8164 if (!ParamOrErr)
8165 return ParamOrErr.takeError();
8166
8167 ASTNodeImporter Importer(*this);
8168 auto ArgPackOrErr =
8169 Importer.ImportTemplateArgument(SubstPack->getArgumentPack());
8170 if (!ArgPackOrErr)
8171 return ArgPackOrErr.takeError();
8172
8173 return ToContext.getSubstTemplateTemplateParmPack(
8174 cast<TemplateTemplateParmDecl>(*ParamOrErr), *ArgPackOrErr);
8175 }
8176 }
8177
8178 llvm_unreachable("Invalid template name kind");
8179}
8180
8181Expected<SourceLocation> ASTImporter::Import(SourceLocation FromLoc) {
8182 if (FromLoc.isInvalid())
8183 return SourceLocation{};
8184
8185 SourceManager &FromSM = FromContext.getSourceManager();
8186 bool IsBuiltin = FromSM.isWrittenInBuiltinFile(FromLoc);
8187
8188 std::pair<FileID, unsigned> Decomposed = FromSM.getDecomposedLoc(FromLoc);
8189 Expected<FileID> ToFileIDOrErr = Import(Decomposed.first, IsBuiltin);
8190 if (!ToFileIDOrErr)
8191 return ToFileIDOrErr.takeError();
8192 SourceManager &ToSM = ToContext.getSourceManager();
8193 return ToSM.getComposedLoc(*ToFileIDOrErr, Decomposed.second);
8194}
8195
8196Expected<SourceRange> ASTImporter::Import(SourceRange FromRange) {
8197 SourceLocation ToBegin, ToEnd;
8198 if (Error Err = importInto(ToBegin, FromRange.getBegin()))
8199 return std::move(Err);
8200 if (Error Err = importInto(ToEnd, FromRange.getEnd()))
8201 return std::move(Err);
8202
8203 return SourceRange(ToBegin, ToEnd);
8204}
8205
8206Expected<FileID> ASTImporter::Import(FileID FromID, bool IsBuiltin) {
8207 llvm::DenseMap<FileID, FileID>::iterator Pos = ImportedFileIDs.find(FromID);
8208 if (Pos != ImportedFileIDs.end())
8209 return Pos->second;
8210
8211 SourceManager &FromSM = FromContext.getSourceManager();
8212 SourceManager &ToSM = ToContext.getSourceManager();
8213 const SrcMgr::SLocEntry &FromSLoc = FromSM.getSLocEntry(FromID);
8214
8215 // Map the FromID to the "to" source manager.
8216 FileID ToID;
8217 if (FromSLoc.isExpansion()) {
8218 const SrcMgr::ExpansionInfo &FromEx = FromSLoc.getExpansion();
8219 ExpectedSLoc ToSpLoc = Import(FromEx.getSpellingLoc());
8220 if (!ToSpLoc)
8221 return ToSpLoc.takeError();
8222 ExpectedSLoc ToExLocS = Import(FromEx.getExpansionLocStart());
8223 if (!ToExLocS)
8224 return ToExLocS.takeError();
8225 unsigned TokenLen = FromSM.getFileIDSize(FromID);
8226 SourceLocation MLoc;
8227 if (FromEx.isMacroArgExpansion()) {
8228 MLoc = ToSM.createMacroArgExpansionLoc(*ToSpLoc, *ToExLocS, TokenLen);
8229 } else {
8230 if (ExpectedSLoc ToExLocE = Import(FromEx.getExpansionLocEnd()))
8231 MLoc = ToSM.createExpansionLoc(*ToSpLoc, *ToExLocS, *ToExLocE, TokenLen,
8232 FromEx.isExpansionTokenRange());
8233 else
8234 return ToExLocE.takeError();
8235 }
8236 ToID = ToSM.getFileID(MLoc);
8237 } else {
8238 const SrcMgr::ContentCache *Cache = FromSLoc.getFile().getContentCache();
8239
8240 if (!IsBuiltin) {
8241 // Include location of this file.
8242 ExpectedSLoc ToIncludeLoc = Import(FromSLoc.getFile().getIncludeLoc());
8243 if (!ToIncludeLoc)
8244 return ToIncludeLoc.takeError();
8245
8246 if (Cache->OrigEntry && Cache->OrigEntry->getDir()) {
8247 // FIXME: We probably want to use getVirtualFile(), so we don't hit the
8248 // disk again
8249 // FIXME: We definitely want to re-use the existing MemoryBuffer, rather
8250 // than mmap the files several times.
8251 const FileEntry *Entry =
8252 ToFileManager.getFile(Cache->OrigEntry->getName());
8253 // FIXME: The filename may be a virtual name that does probably not
8254 // point to a valid file and we get no Entry here. In this case try with
8255 // the memory buffer below.
8256 if (Entry)
8257 ToID = ToSM.createFileID(Entry, *ToIncludeLoc,
8258 FromSLoc.getFile().getFileCharacteristic());
8259 }
8260 }
8261
8262 if (ToID.isInvalid() || IsBuiltin) {
8263 // FIXME: We want to re-use the existing MemoryBuffer!
8264 bool Invalid = true;
8265 const llvm::MemoryBuffer *FromBuf = Cache->getBuffer(
8266 FromContext.getDiagnostics(), FromSM, SourceLocation{}, &Invalid);
8267 if (!FromBuf || Invalid)
8268 // FIXME: Use a new error kind?
8269 return llvm::make_error<ImportError>(ImportError::Unknown);
8270
8271 std::unique_ptr<llvm::MemoryBuffer> ToBuf =
8272 llvm::MemoryBuffer::getMemBufferCopy(FromBuf->getBuffer(),
8273 FromBuf->getBufferIdentifier());
8274 ToID = ToSM.createFileID(std::move(ToBuf),
8275 FromSLoc.getFile().getFileCharacteristic());
8276 }
8277 }
8278
8279 assert(ToID.isValid() && "Unexpected invalid fileID was created.");
8280
8281 ImportedFileIDs[FromID] = ToID;
8282 return ToID;
8283}
8284
8285Expected<CXXCtorInitializer *> ASTImporter::Import(CXXCtorInitializer *From) {
8286 ExpectedExpr ToExprOrErr = Import(From->getInit());
8287 if (!ToExprOrErr)
8288 return ToExprOrErr.takeError();
8289
8290 auto LParenLocOrErr = Import(From->getLParenLoc());
8291 if (!LParenLocOrErr)
8292 return LParenLocOrErr.takeError();
8293
8294 auto RParenLocOrErr = Import(From->getRParenLoc());
8295 if (!RParenLocOrErr)
8296 return RParenLocOrErr.takeError();
8297
8298 if (From->isBaseInitializer()) {
8299 auto ToTInfoOrErr = Import(From->getTypeSourceInfo());
8300 if (!ToTInfoOrErr)
8301 return ToTInfoOrErr.takeError();
8302
8303 SourceLocation EllipsisLoc;
8304 if (From->isPackExpansion())
8305 if (Error Err = importInto(EllipsisLoc, From->getEllipsisLoc()))
8306 return std::move(Err);
8307
8308 return new (ToContext) CXXCtorInitializer(
8309 ToContext, *ToTInfoOrErr, From->isBaseVirtual(), *LParenLocOrErr,
8310 *ToExprOrErr, *RParenLocOrErr, EllipsisLoc);
8311 } else if (From->isMemberInitializer()) {
8312 ExpectedDecl ToFieldOrErr = Import(From->getMember());
8313 if (!ToFieldOrErr)
8314 return ToFieldOrErr.takeError();
8315
8316 auto MemberLocOrErr = Import(From->getMemberLocation());
8317 if (!MemberLocOrErr)
8318 return MemberLocOrErr.takeError();
8319
8320 return new (ToContext) CXXCtorInitializer(
8321 ToContext, cast_or_null<FieldDecl>(*ToFieldOrErr), *MemberLocOrErr,
8322 *LParenLocOrErr, *ToExprOrErr, *RParenLocOrErr);
8323 } else if (From->isIndirectMemberInitializer()) {
8324 ExpectedDecl ToIFieldOrErr = Import(From->getIndirectMember());
8325 if (!ToIFieldOrErr)
8326 return ToIFieldOrErr.takeError();
8327
8328 auto MemberLocOrErr = Import(From->getMemberLocation());
8329 if (!MemberLocOrErr)
8330 return MemberLocOrErr.takeError();
8331
8332 return new (ToContext) CXXCtorInitializer(
8333 ToContext, cast_or_null<IndirectFieldDecl>(*ToIFieldOrErr),
8334 *MemberLocOrErr, *LParenLocOrErr, *ToExprOrErr, *RParenLocOrErr);
8335 } else if (From->isDelegatingInitializer()) {
8336 auto ToTInfoOrErr = Import(From->getTypeSourceInfo());
8337 if (!ToTInfoOrErr)
8338 return ToTInfoOrErr.takeError();
8339
8340 return new (ToContext)
8341 CXXCtorInitializer(ToContext, *ToTInfoOrErr, *LParenLocOrErr,
8342 *ToExprOrErr, *RParenLocOrErr);
8343 } else {
8344 // FIXME: assert?
8345 return make_error<ImportError>();
8346 }
8347}
8348
8349Expected<CXXBaseSpecifier *>
8350ASTImporter::Import(const CXXBaseSpecifier *BaseSpec) {
8351 auto Pos = ImportedCXXBaseSpecifiers.find(BaseSpec);
8352 if (Pos != ImportedCXXBaseSpecifiers.end())
8353 return Pos->second;
8354
8355 Expected<SourceRange> ToSourceRange = Import(BaseSpec->getSourceRange());
8356 if (!ToSourceRange)
8357 return ToSourceRange.takeError();
8358 Expected<TypeSourceInfo *> ToTSI = Import(BaseSpec->getTypeSourceInfo());
8359 if (!ToTSI)
8360 return ToTSI.takeError();
8361 ExpectedSLoc ToEllipsisLoc = Import(BaseSpec->getEllipsisLoc());
8362 if (!ToEllipsisLoc)
8363 return ToEllipsisLoc.takeError();
8364 CXXBaseSpecifier *Imported = new (ToContext) CXXBaseSpecifier(
8365 *ToSourceRange, BaseSpec->isVirtual(), BaseSpec->isBaseOfClass(),
8366 BaseSpec->getAccessSpecifierAsWritten(), *ToTSI, *ToEllipsisLoc);
8367 ImportedCXXBaseSpecifiers[BaseSpec] = Imported;
8368 return Imported;
8369}
8370
8371Error ASTImporter::ImportDefinition(Decl *From) {
8372 ExpectedDecl ToOrErr = Import(From);
8373 if (!ToOrErr)
8374 return ToOrErr.takeError();
8375 Decl *To = *ToOrErr;
8376
8377 auto *FromDC = cast<DeclContext>(From);
8378 ASTNodeImporter Importer(*this);
8379
8380 if (auto *ToRecord = dyn_cast<RecordDecl>(To)) {
8381 if (!ToRecord->getDefinition()) {
8382 return Importer.ImportDefinition(
8383 cast<RecordDecl>(FromDC), ToRecord,
8384 ASTNodeImporter::IDK_Everything);
8385 }
8386 }
8387
8388 if (auto *ToEnum = dyn_cast<EnumDecl>(To)) {
8389 if (!ToEnum->getDefinition()) {
8390 return Importer.ImportDefinition(
8391 cast<EnumDecl>(FromDC), ToEnum, ASTNodeImporter::IDK_Everything);
8392 }
8393 }
8394
8395 if (auto *ToIFace = dyn_cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(To)) {
8396 if (!ToIFace->getDefinition()) {
8397 return Importer.ImportDefinition(
8398 cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(FromDC), ToIFace,
8399 ASTNodeImporter::IDK_Everything);
8400 }
8401 }
8402
8403 if (auto *ToProto = dyn_cast<ObjCProtocolDecl>(To)) {
8404 if (!ToProto->getDefinition()) {
8405 return Importer.ImportDefinition(
8406 cast<ObjCProtocolDecl>(FromDC), ToProto,
8407 ASTNodeImporter::IDK_Everything);
8408 }
8409 }
8410
8411 return Importer.ImportDeclContext(FromDC, true);
8412}

8414Expected<DeclarationName> ASTImporter::Import(DeclarationName FromName) {
8415 if (!FromName)
8416 return DeclarationName{};
8417
8418 switch (FromName.getNameKind()) {
8419 case DeclarationName::Identifier:
8420 return DeclarationName(Import(FromName.getAsIdentifierInfo()));
8421
8422 case DeclarationName::ObjCZeroArgSelector:
8423 case DeclarationName::ObjCOneArgSelector:
8424 case DeclarationName::ObjCMultiArgSelector:
8425 if (auto ToSelOrErr = Import(FromName.getObjCSelector()))
8426 return DeclarationName(*ToSelOrErr);
8427 else
8428 return ToSelOrErr.takeError();
8429
8430 case DeclarationName::CXXConstructorName: {
8431 if (auto ToTyOrErr = Import(FromName.getCXXNameType()))
8432 return ToContext.DeclarationNames.getCXXConstructorName(
8433 ToContext.getCanonicalType(*ToTyOrErr));
8434 else
8435 return ToTyOrErr.takeError();
8436 }
8437
8438 case DeclarationName::CXXDestructorName: {
8439 if (auto ToTyOrErr = Import(FromName.getCXXNameType()))
8440 return ToContext.DeclarationNames.getCXXDestructorName(
8441 ToContext.getCanonicalType(*ToTyOrErr));
8442 else
8443 return ToTyOrErr.takeError();
8444 }
8445
8446 case DeclarationName::CXXDeductionGuideName: {
8447 if (auto ToTemplateOrErr = Import(FromName.getCXXDeductionGuideTemplate()))
8448 return ToContext.DeclarationNames.getCXXDeductionGuideName(
8449 cast<TemplateDecl>(*ToTemplateOrErr));
8450 else
8451 return ToTemplateOrErr.takeError();
8452 }
8453
8454 case DeclarationName::CXXConversionFunctionName: {
8455 if (auto ToTyOrErr = Import(FromName.getCXXNameType()))
8456 return ToContext.DeclarationNames.getCXXConversionFunctionName(
8457 ToContext.getCanonicalType(*ToTyOrErr));
8458 else
8459 return ToTyOrErr.takeError();
8460 }
8461
8462 case DeclarationName::CXXOperatorName:
8463 return ToContext.DeclarationNames.getCXXOperatorName(
8464 FromName.getCXXOverloadedOperator());
8465
8466 case DeclarationName::CXXLiteralOperatorName:
8467 return ToContext.DeclarationNames.getCXXLiteralOperatorName(
8468 Import(FromName.getCXXLiteralIdentifier()));
8469
8470 case DeclarationName::CXXUsingDirective:
8471 // FIXME: STATICS!
8472 return DeclarationName::getUsingDirectiveName();
8473 }
8474
8475 llvm_unreachable("Invalid DeclarationName Kind!");
8476}

8478IdentifierInfo *ASTImporter::Import(const IdentifierInfo *FromId) {
8479 if (!FromId)
8480 return nullptr;
8481
8482 IdentifierInfo *ToId = &ToContext.Idents.get(FromId->getName());
8483
8484 if (!ToId->getBuiltinID() && FromId->getBuiltinID())
8485 ToId->setBuiltinID(FromId->getBuiltinID());
8486
8487 return ToId;
8488}
8489
8490Expected<Selector> ASTImporter::Import(Selector FromSel) {
8491 if (FromSel.isNull())
8492 return Selector{};
8493
8494 SmallVector<IdentifierInfo *, 4> Idents;
8495 Idents.push_back(Import(FromSel.getIdentifierInfoForSlot(0)));
8496 for (unsigned I = 1, N = FromSel.getNumArgs(); I < N; ++I)
8497 Idents.push_back(Import(FromSel.getIdentifierInfoForSlot(I)));
8498 return ToContext.Selectors.getSelector(FromSel.getNumArgs(), Idents.data());
8499}

8509DiagnosticBuilder ASTImporter::ToDiag(SourceLocation Loc, unsigned DiagID) {
8510 if (LastDiagFromFrom)
8511 ToContext.getDiagnostics().notePriorDiagnosticFrom(
8512 FromContext.getDiagnostics());
8513 LastDiagFromFrom = false;
8514 return ToContext.getDiagnostics().Report(Loc, DiagID);
8515}

8517DiagnosticBuilder ASTImporter::FromDiag(SourceLocation Loc, unsigned DiagID) {
8518 if (!LastDiagFromFrom)
8519 FromContext.getDiagnostics().notePriorDiagnosticFrom(
8520 ToContext.getDiagnostics());
8521 LastDiagFromFrom = true;
8522 return FromContext.getDiagnostics().Report(Loc, DiagID);
8523}

8525void ASTImporter::CompleteDecl (Decl *D) {
8526 if (auto *ID = dyn_cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(D)) {
8527 if (!ID->getDefinition())
8528 ID->startDefinition();
8529 }
8530 else if (auto *PD = dyn_cast<ObjCProtocolDecl>(D)) {
8531 if (!PD->getDefinition())
8532 PD->startDefinition();
8533 }
8534 else if (auto *TD = dyn_cast<TagDecl>(D)) {
8535 if (!TD->getDefinition() && !TD->isBeingDefined()) {
8536 TD->startDefinition();
8537 TD->setCompleteDefinition(true);
8538 }
8539 }
8540 else {
8541 assert(0 && "CompleteDecl called on a Decl that can't be completed");
8542 }
8543}
8544
8545Decl *ASTImporter::MapImported(Decl *From, Decl *To) {
8546 llvm::DenseMap<Decl *, Decl *>::iterator Pos = ImportedDecls.find(From);
8547 assert((Pos == ImportedDecls.end() || Pos->second == To) &&
8548 "Try to import an already imported Decl");
8549 if (Pos != ImportedDecls.end())
8550 return Pos->second;
8551 ImportedDecls[From] = To;
8552 // This mapping should be maintained only in this function. Therefore do not
8553 // check for additional consistency.
8554 ImportedFromDecls[To] = From;
8555 return To;
8556}
8557
8558bool ASTImporter::IsStructurallyEquivalent(QualType From, QualType To,
8559 bool Complain) {
8560 llvm::DenseMap<const Type *, const Type *>::iterator Pos =
8561 ImportedTypes.find(From.getTypePtr());
8562 if (Pos != ImportedTypes.end()) {
8563 if (ExpectedType ToFromOrErr = Import(From)) {
8564 if (ToContext.hasSameType(*ToFromOrErr, To))
8565 return true;
8566 } else {
8567 llvm::consumeError(ToFromOrErr.takeError());
8568 }
8569 }
8570
8571 StructuralEquivalenceContext Ctx(FromContext, ToContext, NonEquivalentDecls,
8572 getStructuralEquivalenceKind(*this), false,
8573 Complain);
8574 return Ctx.IsEquivalent(From, To);
8575}
